Rere (ray-ray) in Yoruba means positive, positivity.

Project Rere shares stories about Social Entrepreneurs who are making a difference, particularly in Africa and Asia. Our team aims to shine a light on the positive impact being created by Social Enterpreneurs across global communities.

We are all passionate people, committed to making the world a better place. Read more about us below!

Our Team

Vivek Aswani

The Finance Ninja

Vivek Aswani

The Finance Ninja

A 4th Generation Tolaram Group Family member, Singaporean born but Nigeria raised. He is a serial entrepreneur having started his career in the F&B industry and most recently opened a cocktail bar in Singapore called The Barbary Coast. Vivek currently works in Nigeria as part of the Tolaram Group Beverage division having developed a brand called GoodLife Magik which is a fruit drink aimed at the children in Nigeria.


Having made investments in many companies, Vivek realised that access to finance was needed for Social Entrepreneurs to scale their impact. Project Rere was created to showcase Social Enterprises, busy with saving the world, and to provide them with access to potential grants and investments. Vivek has a MA in Economics and Finance and in his free time loves to go diving and drinking single malt whiskey.

Anusha Aswani

The Social Impact Queen

Anusha Aswani

The Social Impact Queen

Her career first began in Corporate Communications and soon made the switch to Philanthropy. Having initiated various Social Projects in Nigeria, where she grew up, she then decided to pursue her MBA in Social Impact. Anusha has had 8 years in the Impact sphere and is currently running a small Marketing and Distribution company focusing on wholesome food and drink in Singapore.


Not a Quant herself, Anusha has always believed that finance would be able to make the world a better place, and that’s what Project Rere aims to do. In her free time, Anusha is usually found testing out a new recipe or watching her football club, Arsenal, surprise her in one way or another.

Archibald Denis

The Musical Maestro

Archibald Denis

The Musical Maestro

A French born world traveller. Having grown up in Jakarta, Singapore and later the USA. Archibald is a multi instrumentalist musician, at the age of 17 he was accepted on scholarship to Berklee College of Music in Boston MA where he attended Berklee for 4 years graduating with his bachelors in Professional Music.


Archibald has been in numerous bands throughout the years including; Bear Language, Figaro, Grey Area Trio and today he is leading Superjava in his quest to continue to spread his music to the world. Today he writes and produces his music from his home studio located near Bayonne, a town in the South West of France.

Aderinsola Akintilo

The Tech Guru

Aderinsola Akintilo

The Tech Guru

Aderinsola Akintilo is a CEO, consultant, and designer on a mission to build global alliances throughout Nigeria and the African diaspora. He is currently a co-founder of SiriusLabs, a software solutions company specializing in mobile and web applications. He finds himself moonlighting on music, finance, and agriculture projects.


Aderinsola wants to make the world a better place, and by working with ProjectRere he is able to by showing the world that you can help people and make money at the same time. In his free time, you can find Aderinsola swimming in the ocean, playing football, and learning how to build sustainable farms.

Our Advisor

Nitin Vaswani

The Social Finance Doctor

Nitin Vaswani

The Social Finance Doctor

Nitin started his career at Oxley Capital Group, a boutique private equity firm based in Singapore. He advised clients on M&A transactions in the agriculture and healthcare sectors across the Asia-Pacific region. Nitin subsequently completed an MD at the University of Queensland, and pursued specialty training in trauma surgery. During his clinical training, he advised philanthropic foundations on the deployment of safe and cost-effective clinical protocols in their respective healthcare centers. After his clinical training, Nitin completed his MPH and MBA at Johns Hopkins University, where he helped drive research on global surgical safety issues.


More recently, he worked as an Investment Banking Associate at J.P. Morgan’s Healthcare Group, and co-founded a venture capital firm. Nitin was responsible for launching the venture capital firm’s impact investment arm, which advised a variety of family offices on debt and equity transactions in the education and healthcare sectors. Subsequently, Nitin worked in the social investment and innovative financing group of a global NGO named Pact, where he focused on sourcing and completing investments linked to the organization’s mission.
